      "pos": [
        "n."
      ],
      "ety": "[Cf. F. esclave, D. slaaf, Dan. slave, sclave, Sw. slaf, all fr. G. sklave, MHG. also slave, from the national name of the Slavonians, or Sclavonians (in LL. Slavi or Sclavi), who were frequently made slaves by the Germans. See Slav.]",
      "sources": [
        "1913 Webster"
      ],
      "morph": null,
      "usage": [],
      "wordforms": [],
      "entry_synonyms": [],
      "entry_fields": [],
      "senses": [
        {
          "sn": "1.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "A person who is held in bondage to another; one who is wholly subject to the will of another; one who is held as a chattel; one who has no freedom of action, but whose person and services are wholly under the control of another."
          ],
          "quotes": [
            "Art thou our slave, Our captive, at the public mill our drudge?"
          ],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "2.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "One who has lost the power of resistance; one who surrenders himself to any power whatever; as, a slave to passion, to lust, to strong drink, to ambition."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "3.",
          "fields": [],
          "defs": [
            "A drudge; one who labors like a slave."
          ],
          "quotes": [],
          "notes": [],
          "synonyms": []
        },
        {
          "sn": "4.",
          "fields": [
